@database HTMLviewClass
@index "Classes.guide/Main"

@Node Main "RxMUI - HTMLview Class"


HTMLview class    @{"Index" link "Classes.guide/Main"} @{"Super" link "VirtgroupClass.guide/Main"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The HTMLview class creates virtualgroups that show html
  sources.

  The HTMLview class is a subclass of HTMLview.mcc, so you must
  have HTMLview.mcc in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it. HTMLview.mcc is
  copyright of Allan Odgaard.

  From the doc of HTMLview.mcc:

     o Freeware authors can use this gadget for free, as long as
       it isn't distributed together with a commercial product.

     o All others (incl. shareware and commercial) will need to
       obtain a license from the author.

  The above applies as well to ARexx programming, so if you
  release a Shareware or commercial application based on RxMUI
  and HTMLview.mcc you have to ask to Allan Odgaard for a
  license.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}ClickedUrl@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}Contents@{fg text}
  S IS
  Inline html

  @{fg shine}CurrentUrl@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}DiscreteInput@{fg text}
  B IS

  @{fg shine}ImagesInDecodeQueue@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}NoContextMenu@{fg text}
  B I
  Do not add the context menu by default.

  @{fg shine}NTAutoLoad@{fg text}
  B I
  You must handle the loading of the local files.

  @{fg shine}PageID@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}Parsed@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}PropHDeltaFactor@{fg text}
  N N
  A suitable value for DeltaFactor of a horiz Scrollbar
  object.

  @{fg shine}PropVDeltaFactor@{fg text}
  N GN
  A suitable value for DeltaFactor of a vert Scrollbar
  object.

  @{fg shine}Qualifier@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}Target@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}Title@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}Url@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}VLink@{fg text}
  S I
  This is a <64 chars long ARexx stem name used as visited links
  array. Anytime a link is to be drawn, HTMLview checks if that
  link is in VLink.0, ... as it exists. Note that is your job to
  insert the visited links in the array.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Abort@{fg text}
  @{fg shine}ContinueAnims@{fg text}
  @{fg shine}FlushImage@{fg text}
  <name>
  The name of an image or one of:
     o All
     o Displayed
     o NonDisplayed
  @{fg shine}GoToUrl@{fg text}
  url,[target]
  Note that GoUrl is still supported, but obsolete

  @{fg shine}PauseAnim@{fg text}

  @{fg shine}Reload@{fg text}

  @{fg shine}Search@{fg text}
  <string>,[flags]
  flags is a combination of:
     o Case
     o Pattern
     o Back
     o Top
     o Next

@EndNode
